data.title: Vector Capital acquires Showpad, appoints Apratim as CEO, to merge with Bigtincan for growth.
data.description: In San Francisco, Vector Capital Management, L.P. disclosed the finalization of acquiring Showpad, an AI revenue enablement technology front-runner. Apratim Purakayastha has been appointed as the Chief Executive Officer following the transaction's completion. This move merges Showpad with Bigtincan under a single brand to fuel the forthcoming growth phase globally. Vector Capital is a notable technology-focused investment company, while Showpad is known for leading in AI revenue enablement technology. Apratim Purakayastha is to take over as the new CEO.

data.title: CPSC posts recalls on website: Knog recalls bicycle lights (26-051) due to fire and burn hazards. View at www.cpsc.gov.
data.description: On October 30, 2025, the Consumer Product Safety Commission (CPSC) released a statement regarding recent recalls conducted in partnership with various companies. The announcement includes the recall of Knog bicycle lights (recall number: 26-051) due to potential fire and burn hazards. Consumers are urged to visit www.cpsc.gov for more information on these recalls and to ensure their safety.

data.title: MoonPay partners with Mass for bank-to-DeFi transfers in seconds. Collaboration for instant money movement from bank to wallet.
data.description: MoonPay has introduced Virtual Accounts allowing Mass users to transfer funds from their bank to their wallet instantly. The partnership between MoonPay, a top crypto payment platform, and Mass, the prominent on-chain mobile app, aims to streamline the process. This development was publicized in New York on October 30, 2025.

data.title: Hormel Foods' Group VP of Retail Sales, PJ Connor, to retire after 30 years. Natosha Walsh to succeed.
data.description: Natosha Walsh has been named as the successor to PJ Connor after his retirement in AUSTIN, Minnesota on October 30, 2025. Hormel Foods Corporation, a Fortune 500 company trading under the ticker symbol HRL on the New York Stock Exchange, made the announcement regarding the retirement of Connor, who served as the group vice president of Retail sales.

data.title: Docusign integrates AI contract management into ChatGPT through Model Context Protocol (MCP). #AI #Docusign
data.description: In San Francisco on October 30, 2025, Docusign (Nasdaq: DOCU) revealed that its Intelligent Agreement Management (IAM) platform will be integrated into ChatGPT through the Model Context Protocol (MCP). This move by the AI-powered contract management leader is set to provide users access to the capabilities through ChatGPT.

data.title: SITC announces 1,300+ abstracts for 40th Annual Meeting. Numerous clinical late-breaking abstracts included.
data.description: In Milwaukee on October 30, 2025, the Society for Immunotherapy of Cancer (SITC) disclosed that they had an overwhelming response with over 1,300 abstract submissions for the year, inclusive of numerous Late-breaking Abstracts with a focus on clinical aspects. SITC has revealed the titles and authors for the clinical submissions and is thrilled about the exceptional participation.

data.title: Ivonescimab shows positive results with PFS and OS benefits in EGFR+ NSCLC after progression, presented at SITC 2025.
data.description: Hong Kong, 30th October 2025 - Akeso, listed as 9926.HK, has revealed the highly promising outcomes derived from the conclusive overall survival examination of the Phase III HARMONi-A investigation. This study assessed the novel bispecific antibody ivonescimab (PD-1/VEGF bispecific antibody), marking a breakthrough in the field.

data.title: WSFS CARES Foundation donates $50,000 grant to address family homelessness in Delaware, partnering with Social Finance.
data.description: The WSFS CARES Foundation, affiliated with WSFS Financial Corporation (Nasdaq: WSFS), has revealed a $50,000 donation to Social Finance, Inc. This funding supports the initiation of the Family Housing Opportunities for Purposeful Empowerment Project (Family HOPE Project) in New Castle County, Delaware, aiding homeless families in securing housing. This project is a part of WSFS' commitment to community welfare.

data.title: Chewy, a pet supply leader, to acquire SmartEquine from Covetrus, expanding in equine health. SmartEquine offers subscription-based supplements.
data.description: A leading pet company, Chewy, Inc. (NYSE: CHWY) has confirmed the acquisition of SmartPak Equine, LLC (formerly SmartPak), a top U.S. provider of equine health products, from Covetrus, Inc. The deal includes SmartEquine's renowned subscription-based supplement programs, personalized nutrition plans, and extensive tack offerings. SmartPak Equine, rebranded in July 2025, is well-known for its high-quality equine products. This acquisition marks a significant move for Chewy in expanding its reach in the pet industry.
